# Heading and title styles (The Steady Compass)

## Two kinds of headings

1. **Section titles** (e.g. "Today's Market Dashboard", "Market Temperature")
   - **Markup**: Always use `<div class="section-heading">Title text</div>` with `st.markdown(..., unsafe_allow_html=True)`.
   - **Style**: Define and edit only in **`components/nav.py`** inside `inject_nav_css()` as `.section-heading` (e.g. `font-size: 1.35rem !important`).
   - Do **not** add new CSS for section title size in `app.py` or in random `<style>` blocks; it will be inconsistent or overridden.

2. **Small block headers** (e.g. above gauges: "Fear & Greed", "200-Day Disparity")
   - Use the existing class **`.gauge-header-block`** (or similar) and keep its styles in the same file where the block is rendered (e.g. the `<style>` block just above the gauges in `app.py`).

## When adding or changing a section title

- Use the **same** `<div class="section-heading">...</div>` pattern.
- To change the **size or weight** of all section titles, edit **only** `components/nav.py` → `inject_nav_css()` → `.section-heading`.

This keeps one source of truth and avoids "style changes not applying" after multiple attempts.
